  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposal fails to demonstrate that the introduction of a residential use and loss of commercial floorspace compatible with the function of the Major Centre Boundary would support the vitality and viability of this part of the Major Centre Boundary of Streatham contrary to LLP Policy PN4 (Streatham)  and ED7 (Town Centres) of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021) 2020-2035.",
    "The proposed development of the residential unit would be single aspect and fail to provide adequate daylight/sunlight for all habitable rooms.  The proposals would also fail to provide an acceptable level of privacy due to potential overlooking from the lower-ground floor window. The proposal would therefore provide a sub-standard level of accommodation and a poor living environment for future occupants. The application is therefore contrary to Policy D6 of the London Plan (2021) and Policies H5 and Q2 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021) 2020-2035.\r\r",
    "In the absence of a Section 106 Agreement to secure the development as car-permit free, provision of a car club membership and cycle hire membership the transport impacts of the development would not be fully addressed, and it would fail to promote less private car ownership and sustainable travel. The application is therefore contrary to Policies T1, T3 and T6 of the Lambeth Local Plan (2021) 2020-2035."
  ],
